# React Component Library Conventions

Applies to **@forsyteco/product-ui** (`packages/react`). This is a publishable design-system package, not a Next.js application.

## Principles

- Functional components only — no class components.
- Prefer named exports for public components and types.
- Colocate feature code: `component.tsx`, `*.module.css`, `*.test.tsx`, `*.stories.tsx` under `packages/react/src/<feature>/`.
- Minimize `useEffect` and local state when values can be derived from props.
- No data fetching in the library — consumers own server state.

## TypeScript

- Prefer `interface` over `type` for object shapes.
- Avoid `enum` — use const maps.
- Export `*Props` types for public components.
- Avoid new `any` in non-test code.

## Public components

- Use `forwardRef` for interactive primitives where consumers need DOM access (match siblings like `Button`, `Label`).
- Set `displayName` on `forwardRef` and compound subcomponents.
- Use the `function` keyword for top-level pure helpers.

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS 4 and CSS modules (`*.module.css`) — follow patterns in the same feature folder.
- Responsive, mobile-first layouts where layout components need breakpoints.

## File layout

- Directories and files: `lowercase-with-dashes` (e.g. `date-picker/`).
- Refactor when a file grows beyond roughly 200–300 lines.

